license: Apache-2.0
abstract: >-
  MTW TinyLoopScheduler is a header-only cooperative scheduler for AVR
  targets using an Arduino-compatible core. It provides compile-time
  selectable PERIODIC, DELAYED, POSTED, POLL, ISR-deferred, and optional
  PARTED task classes with static storage and automatic dynamic IDLE.
keywords:
  - Arduino
  - AVR
  - embedded systems
  - cooperative scheduling
  - static memory
  - task scheduler